  "texts": [
    "An alternative way to understand the definition of capacitive tendency is to analyse it as the deviation from the ideal of the purely capacitive signal (is easy to recognize).",
    "When the trained model is confident that the curve is close to a rectangle (for CV) or a triangle (for GCD), then this implies that the curve is close to an ideal capacitive signal.",
    "On the contrary, a curve whose confidence value is close to zero means that the curve has a different contribution.",
    "Basically, the capacitive tendency reflects the analysis of the signal shape.",
    "It is information based on a geometric shape."
